<details open="open"><summary class="section-head">Summary</summary>

In an alternate universe, Horus emerged victorious aboard the Vengeful Spirit, having slain the Emperor in a climactic battle that shattered the fabric of the Imperium. Seizing control of the galaxy, he ruthlessly purged the loyalists who remained steadfast in their devotion to the fallen Imperium, forcing those who resisted to confront the seductive power of Chaos. With his newfound dominion, Horus transformed into the Emperor of Chaos, ruling with an iron fist. His reign is marked by an aggressive campaign to reshape humanity, bending it to the will of the dark gods. Under his rule, the Imperium has become a twisted reflection of its former self, where loyalty to Chaos is the only path to survival, and dissent is met with swift and brutal retribution. Horus, now clad in the dark power of Chaos, stands as a God-Emperor, commanding legions of corrupted Space Marines and twisted abominations, determined to usher in a new age of darkness across the galaxy.	

</details><br>

<details open="open"><summary class="section-head">Wargear</summary>

<blockquote>
 
 <h3>The Crown of Chaos</h3>
	This Crown was forged for Horus by the Dark Mechanicum following his victory over the Emperor and subsequent conquest of the Imperium. It features four exquisite gems, each representing one of the Chaos Gods: a ruby for Khorne, a sapphire for Tzeentch, a jade for Nurgle, and an amethyst for Slaanesh. Through these powerful gems, Horus can summon the ruinous powers of Chaos, channeling the dark might of each deity to bolster his dominion over the galaxy.<br><br>
 
	<h3>Serpent's Scales</h3>
	Horus' unique suit of Terminator Armour, known as the Serpent's Scales, was one of the first prototypes of its kind, fashioned by Master Adept Urtzi Malevolus and continuously improved by the hand of the traitorous Fabricator-General of Mars, Kelbor-Hal, and some of the greatest Artificers of the Imperium. It was proof against attacks of both brute and esoteric origin. Sent from Mars to cement the alliance between Horus and the faction of the Mechanicum that would back his rebellion against the Emperor, the armour echoed the colours of the Sons of Horus' elite Justaerin, but it far surpassed them in ornamentation and power. An amber Eye of Horus upon the breastplate stared from the armour's torso and shoulder plates.<br><br>

	<h3>Worldbreaker</h3>
	Worldbreaker was a Power Maul the size of a mortal man marked out with the Imperial Aquila at the base of its grip. As well as being a weapon capable of shattering armoured ceramite, it was also a signifier of Horus' rank as the Warmaster of the Imperium. It is said to have been created by the hand of the Emperor Himself and presented as a gift to his favoured son on the day Horus was raised to become the Warmaster and the Emperor announced that he was returning to Terra.<br><br>
	
	<h3>Warmaster's Talon</h3>
	The Warmaster's Talon is a unique Lightning Claw which incorporated a baroquely styled twin-Bolter that was a precursor of a modern Storm Bolter. The Talon had long been Horus' favoured weapon. Some apocryphal sources claim it was an antediluvian relic that was found deep within the planet Cthonia, and was a product of Mankind's Dark Age of Technology.<br><br>
	
	<h3>The Emperor's Sword</h3>
	This Legendary Sword was wielded by the Emperor himself during the Great Crusade and was seized by Horus after he struck down the Emperor aboard the Vengeful Spirit. With the Emperor's death, the once-radiant blade, which blazed with leaping flames from hilt to tip, has lost its former glory. Now a trophy of conquest, Horus prominently displays the masterfully crafted weapon in his Throne Room, a grim reminder of his triumph over the Imperium’s greatest champion.<br><br>
</blockquote>

